{"questionId":"14344","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A group of 7 adult men wanted to see if there was a relationship between their Body Mass Index (BMI) and their waist size. Their waist sizes, in centimetres, were recorded and their BMI calculated. The following table shows the results.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/8a49ffc98624c7eb7ea169207c9d3ec39c6653e0.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The relationship between <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> can be modelled by the regression equation <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = ax + b\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> and of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp;</em> &nbsp; &nbsp; correct value for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> or <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span> (or for correct <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span> or <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{r^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> = 0.955631 seen in (ii))</p>\n<p>0.141120,&nbsp; 11.1424</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"a\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n</math></span> = 0.141,&nbsp; <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"b\">\n  <mi>b</mi>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;11.1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1 N3</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14344","referenceCode":"19M.2.SL.TZ2.S_1a.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the value of a and of b .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.4—Pearsons, scatter diagrams, eqn of y on x"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}